WEBVTT

00:00:00.020 --> 00:00:04.019
Welcome to this month's edition of JW Broadcasting.

00:00:04.019 --> 00:00:08.019
Here are just a few highlights that we have in store for you.

00:00:08.019 --> 00:00:13.019
Do you feel that you've missed past opportunities to do more for Jehovah?

00:00:13.019 --> 00:00:18.019
Or do you feel that your age or present circumstances keep you from reaching out?

00:00:18.019 --> 00:00:23.019
We'll see how one couple learned that there may be doors of activity available

00:00:23.019 --> 00:00:26.019
to those with a willing spirit.

00:00:26.019 --> 00:00:30.019
Have you ever received an assignment that you felt was overwhelming?

00:00:30.019 --> 00:00:34.020
Brother and sister Hollimey serving in West Africa

00:00:34.020 --> 00:00:37.020
will share what helped them accept such an assignment

00:00:37.020 --> 00:00:41.020
and remain spiritually strong through difficult times.

00:00:41.020 --> 00:00:47.020
And if you're a regular pioneer, what role do you have in strengthening the congregation?

00:00:47.020 --> 00:00:51.020
You'll find this dramatization very insightful.

00:00:52.020 --> 00:00:59.020
Our focus is on our ministry in this May 2018 edition of JW Broadcasting.

00:00:59.020 --> 00:01:21.609
To set this stage for the experiences in our program,

00:01:21.609 --> 00:01:24.609
I'd like to talk to you for a few minutes on the theme,

00:01:24.609 --> 00:01:28.609
Invigorate your ministry, how?

00:01:28.609 --> 00:01:32.609
You dear brothers and sisters are having a regular share in the preaching work

00:01:32.609 --> 00:01:35.609
and just think of the results.

00:01:35.609 --> 00:01:40.609
Each year, about two billion hours are spent in the ministry.

00:01:40.609 --> 00:01:43.609
Millions of Bible studies are conducted

00:01:43.609 --> 00:01:47.609
and those being baptized number into the hundreds of thousands.

00:01:47.609 --> 00:01:53.609
If you are a kingdom publisher, you have had a share in those thrilling statistics.

00:01:53.609 --> 00:01:59.609
But there's a potential danger with so much to do in our life,

00:01:59.609 --> 00:02:05.609
not just in the ministry, but also with secular work, family responsibilities,

00:02:05.609 --> 00:02:10.610
for some even health issues, we can get into a rut.

00:02:10.610 --> 00:02:13.610
It's not always easy to detect it first,

00:02:13.610 --> 00:02:18.610
because in this age of technology, we always feel busy.

00:02:18.610 --> 00:02:21.610
But what consumes our day?

00:02:21.610 --> 00:02:27.610
Watch this one minute video and try to detect what's going on in the life of one brother.

00:02:27.610 --> 00:03:05.539
His life is in a rut. Try to figure out why.

00:03:05.539 --> 00:03:49.740
Would you say that this brother's life is in a rut?

00:03:49.740 --> 00:03:53.740
Oh, he's active all day. He always has something to do.

00:03:53.740 --> 00:03:58.740
But it says if his mind has been kidnapped by his devices.

00:03:58.740 --> 00:04:02.740
Have you ever had the experience of reading an email

00:04:02.740 --> 00:04:05.740
while someone is trying to tell you something?

00:04:05.740 --> 00:04:09.740
It can be embarrassing when you realize that they've asked you a question

00:04:09.740 --> 00:04:11.740
and they're waiting for an answer,

00:04:11.740 --> 00:04:15.740
but you have no idea what they asked. It's embarrassing, right?

00:04:15.740 --> 00:04:21.740
But what if the person who is trying to speak to you is Jehovah?

00:04:21.740 --> 00:04:24.740
Even though we aren't doing anything wrong,

00:04:24.740 --> 00:04:28.740
our daily routine can occupy our attention so much

00:04:28.740 --> 00:04:34.740
that we are not able to hear the refreshing words of Jehovah.

00:04:34.740 --> 00:04:36.740
That can happen to any one of us.

00:04:36.740 --> 00:04:40.740
Even our spiritual activity can get into a rut.

00:04:40.740 --> 00:04:44.740
One Christian sister described it this way.

00:04:44.740 --> 00:04:49.740
I would go out in service, go to meetings, study, pray.

00:04:49.740 --> 00:04:55.740
But I did it all on automatic control, never feeling anything.

00:04:55.740 --> 00:04:58.740
Have you ever felt that way?

00:04:58.740 --> 00:05:01.740
Do you see all the happy servants of Jehovah

00:05:01.740 --> 00:05:05.740
who's experiences appear on JW Broadcasting?

00:05:05.740 --> 00:05:09.740
And you say to yourself, why can't I find that joy?

00:05:09.740 --> 00:05:12.740
Why is my ministry in a rut?

00:05:12.740 --> 00:05:15.740
Perhaps you feel like a remote control train

00:05:15.740 --> 00:05:18.740
that goes around and around on a track,

00:05:18.740 --> 00:05:21.740
working the same territory with the same partner,

00:05:21.740 --> 00:05:24.740
saying the same thing at each door.

00:05:24.740 --> 00:05:28.740
Of course, there's nothing wrong with being in a good routine.

00:05:28.740 --> 00:05:32.740
But being in a rut can sap our energy

00:05:32.740 --> 00:05:35.740
and take the joy out of our service.

00:05:35.740 --> 00:05:39.740
We can even come to view our ministry as boring.

00:05:39.740 --> 00:05:43.740
Of course, we feel invigorated when we get good results.

00:05:43.740 --> 00:05:46.740
We meet an interested person going from door to door.

00:05:46.740 --> 00:05:48.740
We're invigorated.

00:05:48.740 --> 00:05:50.740
And an active person approaches the cart

00:05:50.740 --> 00:05:53.740
and wants to get in touch with the local congregation.

00:05:53.740 --> 00:05:55.740
We're even more invigorated.

00:05:55.740 --> 00:05:57.740
We start a Bible study.

00:05:57.740 --> 00:05:59.740
We're on top of the world.

00:05:59.740 --> 00:06:01.740
I'm sure you'll agree.

00:06:01.740 --> 00:06:04.740
All those outcomes are good reasons for joy.

00:06:04.740 --> 00:06:08.740
The problem is that we're not always in control

00:06:08.740 --> 00:06:10.740
of getting those outcomes.

00:06:10.740 --> 00:06:13.740
In real life, we may spend an entire morning

00:06:13.740 --> 00:06:17.740
in the door-to-door work without meeting an interested person.

00:06:17.740 --> 00:06:20.740
We may spend months making return visits

00:06:20.740 --> 00:06:22.740
without starting a study.

00:06:22.740 --> 00:06:26.740
And once again, our ministry can get into a rut.

00:06:26.740 --> 00:06:28.740
Now, don't misunderstand.

00:06:28.740 --> 00:06:31.740
It's not that we're doing anything wrong.

00:06:31.740 --> 00:06:35.740
But we're not getting the full joy out of doing what's right.

00:06:35.740 --> 00:06:39.740
Of course, Satan would love it if our service to Jehovah

00:06:39.740 --> 00:06:41.740
were to fall into a rut.

00:06:41.740 --> 00:06:44.740
He would love it if we lost our joy.

00:06:44.740 --> 00:06:48.740
If we lose our joy, we lose hope.

00:06:48.740 --> 00:06:50.740
We lose strength.

00:06:50.740 --> 00:06:54.740
And we might even begin to feel like giving up.

00:06:54.740 --> 00:06:57.740
The point is, brothers and sisters,

00:06:57.740 --> 00:07:01.740
if you feel that your ministry has fallen into a rut,

00:07:01.740 --> 00:07:04.740
don't be discouraged and don't give up,

00:07:04.740 --> 00:07:07.740
there are ways that we can invigorate our ministry

00:07:07.740 --> 00:07:11.740
and serve Jehovah with renewed joy.

00:07:11.740 --> 00:07:15.740
To illustrate that, maybe you've had the frustrating experience

00:07:15.740 --> 00:07:19.740
of locking yourself out of your house or apartment.

00:07:19.740 --> 00:07:23.740
Of course, with a key, opening the door is simple.

00:07:23.740 --> 00:07:26.740
A locked door might seem like an obstacle,

00:07:26.740 --> 00:07:29.740
but it isn't if you have the key.

00:07:29.740 --> 00:07:33.740
And the same is true with invigorating our ministry.

00:07:33.740 --> 00:07:35.740
If we've fallen into a rut,

00:07:35.740 --> 00:07:39.740
if we've lost that feeling of joy in our service,

00:07:39.740 --> 00:07:44.740
there are a number of keys that can help us unlock the door.

00:07:44.740 --> 00:07:46.740
Let's look at one.

00:07:46.740 --> 00:07:52.740
Open your Bible to 1 Corinthians chapter 16 verses 8 and 9.

00:07:52.740 --> 00:07:54.740
Now, in these verses,

00:07:54.740 --> 00:07:58.740
the Apostle Paul was presented with the key of opportunity

00:07:58.740 --> 00:08:01.740
and he used it to open a door.

00:08:01.740 --> 00:08:05.740
1 Corinthians 16, 8 and 9 says,

00:08:05.740 --> 00:08:11.740
but I am remaining in Ephesus until the festival of Pentecost

00:08:11.740 --> 00:08:18.740
because a large door that leads to activity has been open to me.

00:08:18.740 --> 00:08:21.740
Here, the Apostle Paul found a key

00:08:21.740 --> 00:08:24.740
and it didn't require moving to another location.

00:08:24.740 --> 00:08:28.740
In this case, the key was to stay where he was

00:08:28.740 --> 00:08:33.740
but to take fuller advantage of an opportunity right before him.

00:08:33.740 --> 00:08:37.740
Sometimes, the key to getting out of a rut in our ministry

00:08:37.740 --> 00:08:42.740
is to take advantage of opportunities we have right where we are.

00:08:42.740 --> 00:08:48.740
For example, have you considered auxiliary pioneering or regular pioneering?

00:08:48.740 --> 00:08:55.740
What about learning a foreign language with the goal of helping a nearby group or congregation?

00:08:55.740 --> 00:09:00.740
Opening one door often leads to other doors of opportunity.

00:09:00.740 --> 00:09:04.740
For example, a brother named Jacob wrote this,

00:09:05.740 --> 00:09:09.740
When I was seven, many of my classmates were Vietnamese.

00:09:09.740 --> 00:09:12.740
I wanted to tell them about Jehovah,

00:09:12.740 --> 00:09:16.740
so after a while, I made plans to learn their language.

00:09:16.740 --> 00:09:19.740
For the most part, I learned by comparing the English

00:09:19.740 --> 00:09:22.740
and Vietnamese editions of the watchtower.

00:09:22.740 --> 00:09:27.740
I also made friends in a nearby Vietnamese language congregation.

00:09:27.740 --> 00:09:30.740
When I was 18, I started pioneering.

00:09:30.740 --> 00:09:33.740
Later, I attended the Bible School for Single Brothers.

00:09:34.740 --> 00:09:37.740
This helped me with my present pioneer assignment

00:09:37.740 --> 00:09:41.740
where I am the only elder in a Vietnamese language group.

00:09:41.740 --> 00:09:46.740
Many Vietnamese people are amazed that I have learned their language.

00:09:46.740 --> 00:09:50.740
They invite me in, and often I can study the Bible with them.

00:09:50.740 --> 00:09:54.740
Some have progressed to baptism.

00:09:54.740 --> 00:09:59.740
The point is, our ministry is what we make it.

00:09:59.740 --> 00:10:03.740
If we allow ourselves to remain in a rut, it will be boring.

00:10:03.740 --> 00:10:08.740
If we use our keys, if we take advantage of opportunities that present themselves,

00:10:08.740 --> 00:10:13.740
we will invigorate our ministry and give it new meaning.

00:10:13.740 --> 00:10:17.740
This doesn't always involve putting in more time in the ministry.

00:10:17.740 --> 00:10:21.740
It could mean that we simply make the best use of our time

00:10:21.740 --> 00:10:25.740
as Ephesians chapter 5 and verse 16 says.

00:10:25.740 --> 00:10:31.740
In fact, there is a saying, don't work harder, work smarter.

00:10:31.740 --> 00:10:36.740
The key to working smarter could be as simple as switching things up a bit.

00:10:36.740 --> 00:10:43.740
For example, could we work with different publishers instead of the same one all the time?

00:10:43.740 --> 00:10:46.740
Could we try a different approach to our presentation,

00:10:46.740 --> 00:10:50.740
perhaps making better use of the Bible or our videos?

00:10:50.740 --> 00:10:53.740
Could we engage in other aspects of the ministry,

00:10:53.740 --> 00:10:56.740
such as cart witnessing or phone witnessing?

00:10:56.740 --> 00:11:03.740
Could we use our time more effectively to reach people when they are most likely to be home?

00:11:03.740 --> 00:11:08.740
Here's something else we could do to unlock a door and invigorate our ministry.

00:11:08.740 --> 00:11:16.740
Open your Bible to Acts chapter 16 verses 9 and 10.

00:11:16.740 --> 00:11:22.740
Now here the Apostle Paul found a unique way to unlock a door to greater joy.

00:11:22.740 --> 00:11:25.740
Acts 16, 9 and 10 says.

00:11:25.740 --> 00:11:29.740
And during the night, a vision appeared to Paul.

00:11:29.740 --> 00:11:33.740
A Macedonian man was standing there urging him and saying,

00:11:33.740 --> 00:11:37.740
step over into Macedonia and help us.

00:11:37.740 --> 00:11:42.740
As soon as he had seen the vision, we tried to go into Macedonia

00:11:42.740 --> 00:11:49.740
drawing the conclusion that God had summoned us to declare the good news to them.

00:11:49.740 --> 00:11:56.740
Notice, Paul didn't think of all the reasons he couldn't step into Macedonia.

00:11:56.740 --> 00:12:01.740
No, he took action as soon as he was presented with the opportunity.

00:12:01.740 --> 00:12:06.740
Paul unlocked the door to invigorate his ministry.

00:12:06.740 --> 00:12:12.740
Sometimes, we think that only those who are young can reach out to pioneer

00:12:12.740 --> 00:12:14.740
or to serve where the need is greater.

00:12:14.740 --> 00:12:17.740
But that's not always the case.

00:12:17.740 --> 00:12:22.740
You parents may be able to unlock a door of opportunity for yourselves

00:12:22.740 --> 00:12:27.740
and think of the example you set for your children when you do so.

00:12:27.740 --> 00:12:32.740
That's what a mother named Tara discovered.

00:12:32.740 --> 00:12:38.740
I started pioneering when my youngest daughter was in elementary school, she says.

00:12:38.740 --> 00:12:43.740
It was important to me that my children see me serving Jehovah

00:12:44.740 --> 00:12:49.740
to the best of my ability as I encouraged them to reach out.

00:12:49.740 --> 00:12:54.740
Tara's husband, Anthony, saw the effect that his wife's pioneering had

00:12:54.740 --> 00:12:57.740
and in time, he too joined the ranks.

00:12:57.740 --> 00:12:59.740
This is what he said.

00:12:59.740 --> 00:13:06.740
When Tara became a pioneer, it made an immediate impact on daughter's number one and number two,

00:13:06.740 --> 00:13:09.740
and they became pioneers.

00:13:09.740 --> 00:13:14.740
When I became a pioneer, daughters number three and number four followed.

00:13:14.740 --> 00:13:23.740
I wish I had pursued full-time service sooner as it made a huge impact on the spirituality of the family.

00:13:23.740 --> 00:13:29.740
I can relate to this experience because of the good example of my parents.

00:13:29.740 --> 00:13:35.740
My mother was baptized in Canada in 1940 when she was 16.

00:13:36.740 --> 00:13:40.740
Jehovah's Witnesses had just been banned in Canada.

00:13:40.740 --> 00:13:45.740
Her father had already died and her mother was opposed at that time.

00:13:45.740 --> 00:13:51.740
The brothers had very little money, but they encouraged my mother to pursue spiritual goals.

00:13:51.740 --> 00:13:59.740
With that encouragement, she started pioneering in 1942 while the ban was still on in Canada.

00:14:00.740 --> 00:14:06.740
In 1947, she was invited to become a special pioneer in the province of Quebec.

00:14:06.740 --> 00:14:14.740
At that time, special pioneers were required to spend 200 hours each month in the ministry.

00:14:14.740 --> 00:14:20.740
With basically no money and no family support, she accepted that assignment.

00:14:20.740 --> 00:14:26.740
This picture was taken when she and her pioneer partner were boarding the train to Quebec.

00:14:27.740 --> 00:14:33.740
Whenever I see this picture, it reminds me of the intrepid spirit that my mother had,

00:14:33.740 --> 00:14:40.740
not being afraid to take on a challenging assignment, but putting complete trust in Jehovah.

00:14:40.740 --> 00:14:45.740
That spirit encourages me even to this day.

00:14:45.740 --> 00:14:47.740
My father has that same spirit.

00:14:47.740 --> 00:14:55.740
In the summer of 1976, when I was 11 years old, a new arrangement was announced at our district convention,

00:14:55.740 --> 00:14:58.740
auxiliary pioneering.

00:14:58.740 --> 00:15:04.740
You could be an auxiliary pioneer if you could devote 60 hours in one month to the ministry.

00:15:04.740 --> 00:15:09.740
The month of October 1976 had five weekends.

00:15:09.740 --> 00:15:15.740
My father encouraged our whole congregation to try auxiliary pioneering that month.

00:15:15.740 --> 00:15:21.740
So many brothers and sisters, including me, decided to get a taste of pioneering.

00:15:21.740 --> 00:15:26.740
It was a wonderful experience that I will never forget.

00:15:26.740 --> 00:15:35.740
Parents, your good example will help your children to have a living ministry of their own that they will love.

00:15:35.740 --> 00:15:42.740
Brothers and sisters, if you find yourself in a rut, there's no reason to stay there.

00:15:42.740 --> 00:15:50.740
We've discussed several ways to reinvigorate our ministry, and with Jehovah's help, we will be successful.

00:15:50.740 --> 00:15:57.740
Now, let's meet a few brothers and sisters who have expanded and invigorated their ministry.

00:15:57.740 --> 00:16:00.740
We're sure you'll appreciate their stories.

00:16:00.740 --> 00:16:05.740
Our first experience comes from Brazil, in South America.

00:16:05.740 --> 00:16:13.740
Cristiano and Joanna Suza found the key to invigorating their ministry in a congregation letter,

00:16:13.740 --> 00:16:19.740
encouraging individuals to apply for the School for Kingdom Evangelizers.

00:16:19.740 --> 00:16:24.740
What new blessings did they experience by reaching out?

00:16:24.740 --> 00:16:36.299
We had our own house, a certain amount of comfort.

00:16:36.299 --> 00:16:41.299
My husband had a stable job, and I was doing a lot where we were.

00:16:41.299 --> 00:16:45.299
I had Bible studies, I was already a regular pioneer.

00:16:45.299 --> 00:16:50.580
So I thought I was doing enough. It was fine to stay there.

00:16:50.580 --> 00:16:56.580
We often see the younger ones going to Bethel, going to serve as special pioneers.

00:16:57.580 --> 00:17:03.580
And once we reached our 40s, I thought that since we're getting older, we wouldn't be able to reach out and do more for Jehovah.

00:17:03.580 --> 00:17:11.579
But after a letter was read to the congregations, that was really the starting point for us to see that we could do more for Jehovah.

00:17:11.579 --> 00:17:16.579
When I heard that there was a school for couples up to 65 years old, I said,

00:17:17.579 --> 00:17:19.579
Cristiano, it's now or never.

00:17:19.579 --> 00:17:23.579
So immediately at the first convention that held a meeting for interested couples,

00:17:23.579 --> 00:17:29.579
we attended the meeting and realized that out of the requirements there was one that my husband didn't meet yet,

00:17:29.579 --> 00:17:33.579
which was two years as a regular pioneer.

00:17:33.579 --> 00:17:36.579
So I thought, why not?

00:17:36.579 --> 00:17:39.579
After the convention, I applied to be a regular pioneer.

00:17:39.579 --> 00:17:42.579
So we made plans to attend the school.

00:17:43.579 --> 00:17:50.579
But we didn't want to stay there waiting to be accepted, as there were no guarantees of being accepted in the same year in which we applied.

00:17:50.579 --> 00:17:54.579
We sold our house, and two weeks later we had sold all the furniture.

00:17:54.579 --> 00:17:58.579
So we made arrangements to serve where the need was greater.

00:17:58.579 --> 00:18:03.589
We took only what was necessary in our car.

00:18:03.589 --> 00:18:07.589
But what is necessary is always too much when you get to the territory.

00:18:07.589 --> 00:18:10.589
You realise you didn't even need everything you took.

00:18:10.589 --> 00:18:13.589
We were really excited because we knew the brothers were expecting us.

00:18:14.589 --> 00:18:21.589
There was a gas station that belonged to a brother, and when we arrived the whole congregation was waiting for us there to welcome us.

00:18:21.589 --> 00:18:22.589
Nine people.

00:18:22.589 --> 00:18:26.589
And that had a great impact on us because we could see the expression on their faces.

00:18:26.589 --> 00:18:28.589
It was if they were asking for help.

00:18:30.990 --> 00:18:33.990
They helped us a lot.

00:18:33.990 --> 00:18:39.990
I can only say that they helped us more than we helped them.

00:18:39.990 --> 00:18:45.880
Now they would be able to have regular meetings.

00:18:45.880 --> 00:18:50.880
The public talk every week, you know, we were in São Paulo and we had all the meetings.

00:18:50.880 --> 00:18:55.880
But in these remote areas they need spiritual food from Jehovah so much.

00:18:55.880 --> 00:18:58.880
But there needs to be people willing to go and help.

00:18:58.880 --> 00:19:05.079
Then one day we had a wonderful surprise.

00:19:05.079 --> 00:19:07.079
A brother called me and said,

00:19:07.079 --> 00:19:10.079
Cristiano, have you checked your emails?

00:19:10.079 --> 00:19:14.079
We'd received a letter inviting us to the school.

00:19:14.079 --> 00:19:17.079
The school really is a gift from Jehovah.

00:19:17.079 --> 00:19:24.079
I've encouraged others I know to attend the school because you really feel how Jehovah cares for his organisation.

00:19:24.079 --> 00:19:29.549
And a small thing we can do is simply give our best.

00:19:29.549 --> 00:19:32.549
And the school helps us to do just that.

00:19:32.549 --> 00:19:34.549
Find out what is our best.

00:19:34.549 --> 00:19:40.119
We were assigned to a congregation called Itido Su.

00:19:40.119 --> 00:19:44.119
The brothers are very loving and we're really happy in our assignment.

00:19:44.119 --> 00:19:50.019
I do miss my house.

00:19:50.019 --> 00:19:54.019
It's nice to have your own house and not to have to worry about paying rent.

00:19:54.019 --> 00:19:57.019
I miss my hairdresser.

00:19:57.019 --> 00:20:02.019
But nothing compares to the blessings and the joy that comes from serving where there's a need.

00:20:02.019 --> 00:20:10.400
This joy helps us to combat any home sickness we feel and stops us from developing any desire to go back home.

00:20:10.400 --> 00:20:14.289
In the big city everything's very rushed.

00:20:14.289 --> 00:20:17.289
I would only see my wife when I got home from work.

00:20:17.289 --> 00:20:20.289
I'd be tired and then also have to care for coronagational matters.

00:20:21.289 --> 00:20:23.289
So there wasn't much time for us to be together.

00:20:23.289 --> 00:20:25.289
Now it's completely different.

00:20:25.289 --> 00:20:30.289
We have much more time during the ministry, in the congregation, being together at home.

00:20:30.289 --> 00:20:36.269
