00:24:06.329 --> 00:24:11.329
But as the trial progressed, things didn't seem to be going so well.

00:24:11.329 --> 00:24:20.329
Last day of the trial, everything changed. We presented a motion and we asked the judge to terminate the case against the brother.

00:24:20.329 --> 00:24:30.329
Personally, I didn't think it would actually work. But one older brother that we worked with over the years, he always told us we need to give you hope of something to bless. And so we did.

00:24:30.329 --> 00:24:38.329
And the results were quite unexpected. When we made the motion, the judge turned to the prosecutor asked, well, what's your opinion?

00:24:38.329 --> 00:24:44.329
And to our surprise, the prosecutor agreed with our request. And he even went beyond what we asked.

00:24:44.329 --> 00:24:50.329
He said to the judge that the government official that started the case against our brother should be punished.

00:24:50.329 --> 00:24:54.329
Well, the judge agreed the case was terminated.

00:24:54.329 --> 00:24:59.329
