00:26:29.329 --> 00:26:35.329
But that wasn't the end of it. As the case continued, a few minutes more, the judge stopped us again.

00:26:35.329 --> 00:26:46.329
And this time the judge said, you know, I'm not sure if Jesus said this. It's in the Bible where he said, where there are two or three gathered together, there I am in your midst.

00:26:46.329 --> 00:26:58.329
But indeed, those are Jesus words. And the judge looked out at this old courtroom, which was filled with our brothers and sisters. And he said, well, Jesus must be in our midst today.

00:26:58.329 --> 00:27:11.329
We felt like breaking into applause. At the end of the court hearing, the judge ruled in our favor, acquitted the brother and the judges and all of the other cases were also acquitted our brothers. It was just a thrilling experience.

00:27:11.329 --> 00:27:28.329
