Many of the segments on our program thus far

00:43:21.190 --> 00:43:25.190
have featured some aspect of preaching in a foreign land.

00:43:25.190 --> 00:43:29.190
If current circumstances don't permit you to serve in this capacity,

00:43:29.190 --> 00:43:33.190
be assured that there's much you can do in your home territory

00:43:33.190 --> 00:43:35.190
to revive your ministry.

00:43:35.190 --> 00:43:41.190
For example, out of the over 100,000 publishers in South Korea,

00:43:41.190 --> 00:43:46.190
there are more than 40,000 zealous regular pioneers.

00:43:46.190 --> 00:43:52.190
What efforts have they made to reach more people in frequently work territory?

00:43:52.190 --> 00:43:55.190
Let's find out.

00:43:55.190 --> 00:43:59.190
I started pioneering less than a year after I got baptized.

00:43:59.190 --> 00:44:02.190
So I was eager to sharpen my preaching skills.

00:44:02.190 --> 00:44:05.190
I really wanted to share my hope with others.

00:44:05.190 --> 00:44:08.190
But it's so hard to meet people at their homes during the day.

00:44:08.190 --> 00:44:13.190
And even if we do meet them, it's not easy to start a conversation.

00:44:13.190 --> 00:44:18.190
Our congregation organized convenience store witnessing from 7am to 9am.

00:44:18.190 --> 00:44:21.190
So I thought this might be a good way to reach people

00:44:21.190 --> 00:44:25.820
and have meaningful conversations.

00:44:25.820 --> 00:44:28.820
But the thing is, I'm not a morning person.

00:44:28.820 --> 00:44:31.820
So getting up early was not easy.

00:44:31.820 --> 00:44:34.820
So I had to make some adjustments.

00:44:34.820 --> 00:44:40.420
I tried not to make plans or stay up late the night before.

00:44:40.420 --> 00:44:45.420
The sample presentations from our meetings were also very helpful.

00:44:45.420 --> 00:44:50.420
In the past, I hardly got the chance to open the Bible while I was preaching.

00:44:50.420 --> 00:44:54.420
But now, I have a few Bible studies.

00:44:54.420 --> 00:44:58.420
Even the time we spend traveling from one convenience store to the next

00:44:58.420 --> 00:45:01.420
is very uplifting spiritually,

00:45:01.420 --> 00:45:05.420
because we use that time to share our preaching skills and build each other up.

00:45:05.420 --> 00:45:08.420
Having a regular share in convenience store witnessing

00:45:08.420 --> 00:45:11.420
has allowed me to be more productive in the ministry.

00:45:11.420 --> 00:45:14.420
I feel like I'm progressing spiritually

00:45:14.420 --> 00:45:18.420
and becoming a better minister of the good news.

00:45:18.420 --> 00:45:22.420
On weekdays, I work to support my family.

00:45:22.420 --> 00:45:26.420
So I would usually go out and field service on the weekends.

00:45:26.420 --> 00:45:30.420
But it wasn't easy to find people at their homes,

00:45:30.420 --> 00:45:33.420
because they usually make plans and go out.

00:45:33.420 --> 00:45:37.420
And you know, it's hard to get excited about the preaching work

00:45:37.420 --> 00:45:40.420
when you're not meeting many people.

00:45:40.420 --> 00:45:43.420
I wanted to set a good example for my family,

00:45:43.420 --> 00:45:48.420
but I found it a real challenge to maintain my zeal for the ministry.

00:45:49.420 --> 00:45:53.420
So I began to regularly participate in evening witnessing

00:45:53.420 --> 00:45:56.420
on Mondays, Tuesdays, and Fridays.

00:45:56.420 --> 00:46:00.420
I usually get off work around 5 p.m.

00:46:00.420 --> 00:46:02.420
After a long day at work,

00:46:02.420 --> 00:46:07.420
it's not always easy to get dressed to go out in the field ministry.

00:46:07.420 --> 00:46:10.420
But I kept up with my return visits

00:46:10.420 --> 00:46:13.420
and had some really encouraging experiences.

00:46:13.420 --> 00:46:17.420
A young man I had been visiting accepted a Bible study

00:46:17.420 --> 00:46:19.420
and he's making fine progress.

00:46:19.420 --> 00:46:24.420
My children were able to see how much joy I get from the ministry.

00:46:24.420 --> 00:46:27.420
And so now, they too are able to give a bold witness

00:46:27.420 --> 00:46:31.420
in their own words, even in the face of opposition.

00:46:31.420 --> 00:46:35.420
I am very proud of my children, training and teaching them

00:46:35.420 --> 00:46:38.420
how to make effective return visits and Bible studies

00:46:38.420 --> 00:46:41.420
brings me great joy.

00:46:41.420 --> 00:46:45.420
We serve in a small rural town where many leave home early in the morning

00:46:45.420 --> 00:46:48.420
to work in the field and they return late at night.

00:46:48.420 --> 00:46:52.420
So it's not easy to find people at home during the daytime.

00:46:52.420 --> 00:46:54.420
And even if we do find them at their doors,

00:46:54.420 --> 00:46:58.420
it's not easy to develop a meaningful Bible-based conversation.

00:46:58.420 --> 00:47:02.420
Let alone make return visits and conduct Bible studies with them.

00:47:02.420 --> 00:47:06.420
After returning home from preaching at night, I would ask myself,

00:47:06.420 --> 00:47:09.420
did I have a meaningful share in the ministry today?

00:47:09.420 --> 00:47:12.420
It's a small rural town.

00:47:12.420 --> 00:47:15.420
So many people are concerned about what their neighbors would think

00:47:15.420 --> 00:47:17.420
if they talked with us.

00:47:17.420 --> 00:47:21.420
So even those who are interested in learning more about the Bible

00:47:21.420 --> 00:47:25.420
were reluctant to have Bible discussions with us.

00:47:25.420 --> 00:47:29.420
It was really unfortunate.

00:47:29.420 --> 00:47:33.420
We tried to figure out the right time to call on people.

00:47:33.420 --> 00:47:36.420
And we found out that many householders are more relaxed

00:47:36.420 --> 00:47:39.420
than willing to talk about the Bible.

00:47:39.420 --> 00:47:45.420
So if we visit them around 9 or 10 o'clock in the evening,

00:47:45.420 --> 00:47:48.420
I gave much thought on how I could help my Bible students

00:47:48.420 --> 00:47:51.420
have a regular intake of spiritual food.

00:47:51.420 --> 00:47:55.420
One of my students worked from 9 a.m. to 10 p.m.

00:47:55.420 --> 00:47:59.420
So I asked her if we can arrange to study early in the morning.

00:47:59.420 --> 00:48:01.420
She agreed.

00:48:01.420 --> 00:48:03.420
I often tell my Bible students,

00:48:03.420 --> 00:48:08.420
just call me whenever you have a little time to talk.

00:48:09.420 --> 00:48:12.420
When I get those calls, no matter what time it is,

00:48:12.420 --> 00:48:17.500
it's time to rush out that door.

00:48:17.500 --> 00:48:20.500
There was one elderly lady who was in her early 80s

00:48:20.500 --> 00:48:24.500
who had attended church all her life.

00:48:24.500 --> 00:48:29.500
To accommodate her needs, I visited her around 9 or 10 o'clock

00:48:29.500 --> 00:48:33.500
in the evening for our Bible studies.

00:48:33.500 --> 00:48:37.500
I come home feeling tired and hungry,

00:48:37.500 --> 00:48:42.500
but the satisfaction of knowing that I've helped her learn more about the truth

00:48:42.500 --> 00:48:45.500
enables me to maintain my joy.

00:48:45.500 --> 00:48:50.750
Now I'm able to conduct about 12 Bible studies.

00:48:50.750 --> 00:48:54.750
I try to become all things to people of all sorts

00:48:54.750 --> 00:48:57.750
in order to look after their needs.

00:48:57.750 --> 00:49:01.750
And it brings me great satisfaction and joy to see my studies make progress

00:49:01.750 --> 00:49:06.750
because that's really how Jehovah wants us to be carrying out our ministry.

00:49:08.750 --> 00:49:14.539
You might feel that you've worked every corner of your home territory,

00:49:14.539 --> 00:49:19.539
but just like a literal fisherman adapts to the time when the fish are biting,

00:49:19.539 --> 00:49:22.539
we need to work when people can be found.

00:49:22.539 --> 00:49:26.539
Cast your nets into productive waters.

00:49:26.539 --> 00:49:33.539
Our sister arranged her schedule to call on her Bible student at 9 or 10 in the evening.

00:49:33.539 --> 00:49:38.539
Of course, we want to use good judgment to call it times that are both practical

00:49:38.539 --> 00:49:41.539
and safe for our territory.

00:49:41.539 --> 00:49:47.539
But by being adaptable to when, where or how we preach the good news,

00:49:47.539 --> 00:49:52.539
we may yield good results like our fellow witnesses in South Korea.

00:49:52.539 --> 00:49:57.539
This will help us to have a meaningful share in the all-important work

00:49:57.539 --> 00:50:02.539
of finding those who are rightly disposed for everlasting life.

00:50:02.539 --> 00:50:08.889
Regular pioneers work in a powerful way to help their brothers and sisters

00:50:08.889 --> 00:50:11.889
get the most out of their ministry.

00:50:11.889 --> 00:50:17.889
But does that mean that they're impervious to being in a rut, as mentioned earlier?

00:50:17.889 --> 00:50:22.889
In the following dramatization, see how one pioneer sister comes to realize

00:50:22.889 --> 00:50:26.889
the need to adjust her approach to the field ministry.

00:50:26.889 --> 00:50:46.019
It was really nice of Maria to invite me in service,

00:50:46.019 --> 00:50:51.260
but I already have plans with Sarah.

00:50:51.260 --> 00:51:04.780
We have similar service schedules, and we really enjoy working together.

00:51:04.780 --> 00:51:17.699
I try to get most of my time during the week.

00:51:17.699 --> 00:51:23.059
Anyone made plans to work together?

00:51:23.059 --> 00:51:26.059
Though I do meet with the group sometimes on Saturday.

00:51:26.059 --> 00:51:33.960
Sister Martin, thanks everyone.

00:51:33.960 --> 00:51:35.960
Anyone made plans to work together?

00:51:35.960 --> 00:51:41.659
Okay, Joanna, you can work with Sarah.

00:51:41.659 --> 00:51:51.019
Anyone made plans to work together?

00:51:51.019 --> 00:51:53.019
Could I work with Alicia?

00:51:53.019 --> 00:51:55.019
Uh-huh.

00:51:55.019 --> 00:51:58.019
Joanna, could you two work together, please?

00:51:58.019 --> 00:52:02.019
I'd love to, but I've just arranged to work with Sarah.

00:52:02.019 --> 00:52:04.019
I'm so sorry.

00:52:04.019 --> 00:52:06.019
No problem.

00:52:06.019 --> 00:52:08.019
Maria, could you work with this sister?

00:52:08.019 --> 00:52:31.780
While doing my Bible reading that night,

00:52:31.780 --> 00:52:38.780
I was really affected by the words found at 2nd Corinthians 6, 12, and 13.

00:52:38.780 --> 00:52:42.780
You are restricted in your own tender affections.

00:52:42.780 --> 00:52:44.780
Open your heart's wide.

00:52:44.780 --> 00:52:55.550
It struck me that some in the congregation missed out on a beautiful blessing

00:52:55.550 --> 00:52:58.550
by drawing away from the Apostle Paul.

00:52:58.550 --> 00:53:06.170
I realized I was limiting my joy as well,

00:53:06.170 --> 00:53:10.170
by not working with more in the ministry.

00:53:10.170 --> 00:53:13.170
I was going through the motions of pioneering,

00:53:13.170 --> 00:53:16.170
but I was stuck in the same routine.

00:53:16.170 --> 00:53:18.170
How are you, Maria?

00:53:18.170 --> 00:53:19.170
Good.

00:53:19.170 --> 00:53:20.170
And you?

00:53:20.170 --> 00:53:21.170
Let me ask you something.

00:53:21.170 --> 00:53:23.170
Could you join me on a Bible study Saturday?

00:53:23.170 --> 00:53:24.170
Oh, I'd love that.

00:53:24.170 --> 00:53:25.170
That's great.

00:53:25.170 --> 00:53:27.170
So later we'll make the arrangements, okay?

00:53:27.170 --> 00:53:28.170
Exactly.

00:53:36.250 --> 00:53:41.250
My student liked Maria and Isabelle so much.

00:53:41.250 --> 00:53:44.250
I really learned a lot from them.

00:53:44.250 --> 00:53:55.230
I started going out regularly on the weekends.

00:53:55.230 --> 00:53:57.230
Anyone made plans to work together?

00:53:57.230 --> 00:54:04.300
And working with different ones in the ministry.

00:54:04.300 --> 00:54:09.300
And I learned more about Sister Martin after one day in the ministry

00:54:09.300 --> 00:54:14.300
than I had in years of seeing her at meetings.

00:54:14.300 --> 00:54:18.300
Sarah and I still enjoy working together.

00:54:18.300 --> 00:54:22.300
But I found that by working with a variety of friends,

00:54:22.300 --> 00:54:37.619
my own joy has increased.

00:54:37.619 --> 00:54:41.619
I'm so glad I opened my heart wide.

00:54:41.619 --> 00:54:52.110
Joanna came to realize that her privilege of full-time service

00:54:52.110 --> 00:54:55.110
was more than just hours and a schedule.

00:54:55.110 --> 00:54:58.110
By working with a variety of sisters in the ministry

00:54:58.110 --> 00:55:01.110
and supporting her field service group,

00:55:01.110 --> 00:55:04.110
she could strengthen and encourage others.

00:55:04.110 --> 00:55:07.110
It was within her power to help,

00:55:07.110 --> 00:55:09.110
but with what result?

00:55:09.110 --> 00:55:12.110
It rejuvenated her ministry.

00:55:12.110 --> 00:55:17.110
We truly appreciate the love and sacrifice of our pioneers.

00:55:18.110 --> 00:55:22.110
Have you been inspired to make a change in your ministry?

00:55:22.110 --> 00:55:26.110
Whether big or small, at home or abroad,

00:55:26.110 --> 00:55:29.110
we can find the satisfaction that comes from

00:55:29.110 --> 00:55:32.110
re-envigorating our ministry.

00:55:32.110 --> 00:55:35.110
That's the theme featured in the music video entitled,

00:55:35.110 --> 00:55:37.110
I'm Making a Change.

00:55:37.110 --> 00:56:00.579
My serving Jehovah through the same routine.

00:56:00.579 --> 00:56:15.699
The things that I'm doing in a change

00:56:15.699 --> 00:59:43.929
are taking some changes along for trusting in you.

00:59:43.929 --> 00:59:46.929
The governing body deeply appreciates the work

00:59:46.929 --> 00:59:48.929
of each kingdom publisher.

00:59:48.929 --> 00:59:52.929
You dear brothers and sisters are having a regular share

00:59:52.929 --> 00:59:55.929
in the preaching work, and we commend you for that.

00:59:55.929 --> 00:59:59.929
You can be sure that God is not unrighteous

00:59:59.929 --> 01:00:01.929
so as to forget your work,

01:00:01.929 --> 01:00:04.929
and the love you showed for His name,

01:00:04.929 --> 01:00:08.929
as the Bible says at Hebrews chapter 6 and verse 10.

01:00:08.929 --> 01:00:12.929
Just knowing that can help us to take a fresh look

01:00:12.929 --> 01:00:15.929
at our ministry and can invigorate us

01:00:15.929 --> 01:00:19.929
to participate to the fullest extent.

01:00:19.929 --> 01:00:25.929
To conclude, we bring you greetings from Bosnia and Herzegovina.

01:00:25.929 --> 01:00:28.929
This mountainous region has a rich history

01:00:28.929 --> 01:00:31.929
as a traditional meeting place between Eastern

01:00:31.929 --> 01:00:35.929
and Western cultures dating from the Middle Ages.

01:00:35.929 --> 01:00:39.929
Because of the diverse religious beliefs within the country,

01:00:39.929 --> 01:00:44.929
the 1,160 publishers must adapt their preaching methods

01:00:44.929 --> 01:00:48.929
to appeal to the hearts of those who listen.

01:00:48.929 --> 01:00:53.929
This is the city of Mostar, which sits on the Neretva River.

01:00:53.929 --> 01:00:58.929
The Neretva River flows for nearly 230 kilometers

01:00:58.929 --> 01:01:01.929
or almost 144 miles.

01:01:01.929 --> 01:01:06.929
Mostar was a former front line during the wars of the 1990s

01:01:06.929 --> 01:01:10.929
and many buildings still bear the marks of the intense fighting

01:01:10.929 --> 01:01:12.929
that took place.

01:01:12.929 --> 01:01:16.929
Likewise, the aftermath left many people in this region

01:01:16.929 --> 01:01:19.929
with emotional and mental scars.

01:01:19.929 --> 01:01:22.929
Our brothers and sisters are working hard

01:01:22.929 --> 01:01:27.929
to bring the hope of something good to those in need.

01:01:27.929 --> 01:01:32.929
In the 1930s, a pioneer brother named Alfred Tuchek

01:01:32.929 --> 01:01:36.929
spearheaded the preaching work in the city of Mostar.

01:01:36.929 --> 01:01:41.929
He was actually one of the first in the former Yugoslavia to pioneer.

01:01:41.929 --> 01:01:46.929
Today, the congregation in Mostar has about 60 publishers,

01:01:46.929 --> 01:01:51.929
including nine pioneers and four field missionaries.

01:01:51.929 --> 01:01:56.929
They bring their warm love and greetings to all of us around the world.

01:01:56.929 --> 01:02:00.929
This is JW Broadcasting from the World Headquarters

01:02:00.929 --> 01:02:03.929
of Jehovah's Witnesses.
